sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Dashboard
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant RBAC as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant API as DS Pipeline API Server<br/>8888/TCP HTTP(S)
    participant DB as MariaDB<br/>3306/TCP MySQL TLS
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>HTTPS/HTTP
    participant Argo as Argo Workflow Controller
    participant Launcher as KFP Launcher/Driver Pod
    participant MLMD as MLMD gRPC Server<br/>8080/TCP gRPC mTLS
    participant Envoy as MLMD Envoy Proxy<br/>9090/TCP gRPC-Web

    Note over User,S3: Flow 1: Pipeline Submission & Execution

    User->>Route: POST /apis/v2beta1/pipelines<br/>Bearer Token
    Route->>RBAC: Reencrypt TLS
    RBAC->>RBAC: SubjectAccessReview<br/>(datasciencepipelinesapplications/api)
    RBAC->>API: Forward (HTTP or HTTPS<br/>if PodToPodTLS)
    API->>DB: Store pipeline metadata<br/>MySQL TLS (if PodToPodTLS)<br/>Username/Password
    API->>S3: Store pipeline artifact<br/>TLS 1.2+<br/>Access Key / Secret Key
    API->>Argo: Create Workflow CR<br/>via K8s API (RBAC)
    Argo->>Launcher: Create Launcher/Driver pods<br/>via K8s API

    Note over Launcher,MLMD: Flow 2: ML Metadata Access (during pipeline execution)

    Launcher->>MLMD: Record artifacts/lineage<br/>gRPC 8080/TCP<br/>mTLS (if PodToPodTLS)<br/>NetworkPolicy enforced
    MLMD->>DB: Store metadata<br/>MySQL TLS<br/>Username/Password

    Note over User,Envoy: Flow 3: Dashboard MLMD Access

    User->>Route: GET metadata<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    Route->>RBAC: Reencrypt TLS
    RBAC->>Envoy: gRPC-Web 9090/TCP<br/>localhost (no auth)
    Envoy->>MLMD: gRPC 8080/TCP<br/>TLS (if PodToPodTLS)
    MLMD-->>Envoy: Metadata response
    Envoy-->>RBAC: gRPC-Web response
    RBAC-->>Route: Response
    Route-->>User: JSON/Protobuf

    Note over User,S3: Flow 4: DSPA Reconciliation (Operator)

    participant K8sAPI as K8s API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant DSPO as DSPO Controller
    participant OCI as OCI Registry<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    K8sAPI->>DSPO: Watch DSPA CR change<br/>ServiceAccount token
    DSPO->>DB: Health check<br/>MySQL TLS (configurable)
    DB-->>DSPO: Connection OK
    DSPO->>S3: Health check<br/>TLS 1.2+ (configurable)
    S3-->>DSPO: Connection OK
    DSPO->>OCI: Fetch managed pipelines<br/>HTTPS TLS
    OCI-->>DSPO: Pipeline manifests (OCI layers)
    DSPO->>K8sAPI: Apply manifests (Manifestival)<br/>ServiceAccount token
